---
import Heading from "@components/Heading.astro";
import HeadingLarge from "@components/HeadingLarge.astro";
import Text from "@components/Text.astro";
import View from "@components/View.astro";
import Group from "@components/Group.astro";
import { Layout } from "@layouts";
import Image from "@components/Image.astro";
import HeadingSmall from "@components/HeadingSmall.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Moneytree | Jonathon Toon | Software Designer, Product Leader"
  description="Jonathon Toon is a versatile software designer and product leader based in Aotearoa New Zealand."
  keywords="design, software, product, fractional, leadership, new zealand, aotearoa, technology, typescript, start ups, engineering, mentorship, coaching, adplist"
  twitterHandle="@jonathontoon"
  canonicalUrl="https://www.jonathontoon.com/"
  ogImage="/images/og-image.png"
>
  <Group>
    <HeadingLarge class="px-2">Moneytree</HeadingLarge>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Founded in 2012 as one of the first personal finance apps of its kind in
      Japan (named Apple’s App of the Year for 2013) Moneytree grew to serve
      over 6.5 million users.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Its open banking platform, Moneytree Link, now the core of the business,
      connects to more than 2,500 financial institutions and supports 120
      enterprise customers.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I first joined as a Senior Product Designer in 2016 before becoming
      Product & Design Lead, where I drove hands-on product and design efforts
      for the Moneytree Link platform.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Later I returned in 2021 as Director of Design to build and scale the
      design team, expanding my remit to become Director of Discovery, leading
      the business vertical focused on incubating 0-to-1 products and enterprise
      customer growth.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <View class="px-2">
      <View class="h-px w-full bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-700" />
    </View>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Moneytree Business</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I assembled and led a product team through a six-month 0-1 process to
      create Moneytree Business. I was responsible for all outcomes and output.
      Whether creative, financial or technical.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Together we conducted over 30 interviews with accountants and business
      owners across Japan. Alongside this we followed through with market
      research around economic risks to identify the biggest operational
      challenges, as well as sentiment around cost and pricing.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      What we found was quite painful. Japanese business owners spent 30 hours
      per week on manual financial tasks. They visited ATMs to confirm
      transactions. They reconciled receipts by hand. They dealt with frustrated
      accountants calling about incorrect data.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      All time that should have been spent with customers.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-business-home-desktop.png"
      alt="Dashboard showing business financial data categorization and cash flow insights."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Our initial audience centered around businesses up to 60 employees, in
      industries such as heavy machinery to import goods.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      They had two core needs which manifested as primary functions in the
      product: monitoring cashflow and preparing clean data for their
      accountants.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      We iterated constantly on these core features based on regular feedback
      sessions or asynchronous inputs from these business owners. By avoiding
      hypothetical personas, and simply cultivating relationships with early
      adopters we were able to understand exactly what they needed.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-business-cashflow-desktop.png"
      alt="Real-time cash flow visualization with predictive analytics."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-business-export-desktop.png"
      alt="Data export functionality for seamless accountant collaboration."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      The secondary opportunity was categorization. By repurposing Moneytree's
      existing machine learning technology, new patterns emerged for these
      business owners. Things they had never seen from their banks or
      accountants. This became valuable for events like cost reduction and
      planning new hires.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-business-categories-desktop.png"
      alt="Machine learning-powered transaction categorization revealing spending patterns."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-business-account-desktop.png"
      alt="Multi-account overview connecting 2,500+ financial institutions."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      We chose not to build a responsive product at launch. Even though it came not
      long after. This was quite controversial internally but it made sense
      strategically.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I made the call based on what we knew. Most of the business owners we
      spoke with were looking for ways to avoid leaving their place of business.
      For they worked at desks, not on phones.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-business-mobile.png"
      alt="Mobile-optimized experience for on-the-go business management."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Only a month after its launch the product hit ¥2M ARR and maintained
      strong growth, surpassing revenue of previous efforts in to small business
      products. The company's renewed focus on small businesses also opened some
      interesting new partnerships, including a lending product with a major
      credit card company.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      When MUFG Bank, Ltd. acquired Moneytree in 2025, they specifically cited
      Moneytree Business growth as one of the reasons they were confident and
      excited about the purchase.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Moneytree LINK</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Moneytree LINK was one of Japan's first Open Banking platforms. It set the blueprint for financial data legislation in the country.
      </Text> 
          <Text class="px-2">
      Think Plaid, but for Japan.
      </Text> 
    <Text class="px-2">
      We provided data aggregation services and the sharing infrastructure to fintech startups, lending companies, insurance firms, and Japan's big three banks.
    </Text>
        <Text class="px-2">
      The product combined three key components: a REST API, native SDKs, and two web interfaces. Together, they let end users connect their financial accounts, control what data they shared, and enabled our customers to receive that data seamlessly.
    </Text>
        <Text class="px-2">
      During my time at Moneytree I lead the creation for some of these key products.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <HeadingSmall class="px-2">Moneytree ID</HeadingSmall>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-link-vault.png"
      alt="Secure data vault for financial institution connectivity."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-link-service.png"
      alt="Enterprise banking API management and monitoring tools."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
        <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-link-signin.png"
      alt="Streamlined authentication flow for bank account linking."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-link-auth.png"
      alt="Streamlined authentication flow for bank account linking."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <HeadingSmall class="px-2">Fast Onboarding</HeadingSmall>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-link-fast-onboarding.png"
      alt="Optimized onboarding reducing setup time from minutes to seconds."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-link-fast-onboarding-branded.png"
      alt="White-label onboarding experience for enterprise partners."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <HeadingSmall class="px-2">Isshou Tsucho</HeadingSmall>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-link-isshou-tsucho.png"
      alt="Isshou Tsucho bank integration showcasing API versatility."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Moneytree for iOS</Heading>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-ios.png"
      alt="iOS redesign focusing on improved navigation and data visualization."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
</Layout>
